# text = Every evening, when his work was ended, he supped on a little biscuit, moistened in water, a sea-urchin or a crab, or a few _châtaignes de mer_, the only food to be found among those rocks; and shivering like his knotted cord, mounted again to sleep in his cell upon the Great Douvre.
